<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1260,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,490,1260,1287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[525,793,1262,1287]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis box="[525,793,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in a restricted area between 1320 and 
<quantity box="[1330,1418,1261,1288]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" unit="m" value="1450.0">1450 m</quantity>
of elevation, at the Scala di Gaudolino (Pollino Massif), Morano Calabro (Cosenza province), in the Pollino National Park (
<figureCitation box="[206,275,1333,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,2027,2049]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,929,2002]" captionTargetId="figure-395@1.[214,1373,929,2002]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. The single known location of Hieracium terraccianoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). From a bioclimatic point of view, according to the terminology of Rivas-Martinez (1981), the area falls within the supramediterranean bioclimatic belt with the lower humid ombrotype. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[1133,1400,1370,1395]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis box="[1133,1400,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a calcicolous taxon, represented by about 300 individuals growing on NW-facing rocks and stony slopes, in clearings of the beech forest (
<figureCitation box="[329,398,1441,1467]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1065,1087]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,190,1041]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[227,1361,190,1041]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Carbonate rocks and stony slopes of Scala di Gaudolino, the habitat of Hieracium terraccianoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147155/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1260,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,426,1476,1503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Conservation status</emphasis>
:—According to the 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[654,804,1477,1503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref2966" refString="IUCN (2010) The IUCN Red List of threatened species, version 2010.4. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge, UK. Available: http: // www. iucnredlist. org. (accessed 25 May 2013)." type="url" year="2010">IUCN (2010)</bibRefCitation>
criteria for the conservation status assessment, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR): B1a+2a; C2a(ii).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1260,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,476,1548,1574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Taxonomic relationship</emphasis>
:—Bract indumentum (appearing greyish because of the presence of many stellate hairs and but few glandular hairs) and the bluish green, spotted leaves suggest a possible relationship of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with species of 
<emphasis box="[455,483,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Arvet-Touvet 1880: 287) Clapham (1952: 1153)" authorityName="Clapham" authorityPageNumber="1153" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Arvet-Touvet" baseAuthorityPageNumber="287" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[547,1172,1621,1648]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Bifida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,615,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Bifida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Arvet-Touvet, C." box="[629,902,1621,1647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="278 - 292" refId="ref2092" refString="Arvet-Touvet, C. (1880) Essai de classification sur les genres Pilosella &amp; Hieracium. Bulletin de la Societe Dauphinoise pour l'Echange des Plantes 7: 278 - 292." type="journal article" year="1880">Arvet-Touvet 1880: 287</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Clapham, A. R. &amp; Tutin, T. G. &amp; Warburg, E. F." box="[917,1172,1621,1648]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref2339" refString="Clapham, A. R., Tutin, T. G. &amp; Warburg, E. F. (1952) Flora of the British Isles. University Press, Cambridge, 1591 pp." type="book" year="1952">Clapham (1952: 1153)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The long narrowed base of the basal leaves and the presence of 2, sometimes 3 stem leaves (with the lowest stem leaf often being inserted only 
<quantity box="[136,221,1693,1719]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" unit="cm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 cm</quantity>
above the rosette leaves) show some similarity with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fries 1819: 76) Fries (1845: 7)" authorityName="Fries" authorityPageNumber="7" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Fries" baseAuthorityPageNumber="76" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[832,1336,1693,1720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caesium">
<emphasis box="[832,960,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. caesium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fries, E." box="[977,1145,1693,1720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="73 - 80" refId="ref2495" refString="Fries, E. (1819) Novitiae Florae Svecicae. Part V. Continuatio. Berlingianis, Lund, pp. 73 - 80." type="book chapter" year="1819">Fries 1819: 76</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Fries, E." box="[1162,1336,1693,1720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref2521" refString="Fries, E. (1845) Summa Vegetabilium Scandinaviae. Typographia Academica, Uppsala, 258 pp." type="book" year="1845">Fries (1845: 7)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fries" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Fries" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[136,266,1730,1755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caesium">
<emphasis box="[136,266,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. caesium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has its main distribution in N Europe, where it has evolved postglacially. Direct relationship across a disjunction between N Europe and 
<collectingRegion box="[533,631,1765,1791]" country="Italy" name="Calabria" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Calabria</collectingRegion>
, implying a relict state for 
<emphasis box="[934,1114,1766,1791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[934,1110,1766,1791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">H. terraccianoi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
is an improbable assumption. Therefore the morphological traits suggesting such an affinity (number of stem leaves, bract indumentum) result from analogy. The winged petioles of the lower stem leaf and the semiamplexicaul base of the upper stem leaf (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1401,1837,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[178,1412,175,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-29@2.[176,1412,175,1989]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hieracium terraccianoi: Holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147151/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) are more important features, as they indicate membership in 
<emphasis box="[792,820,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[888,1018,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Grovesiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gottschlich, G." box="[1027,1315,1873,1900]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 328" refId="ref2675" refString="Gottschlich, G. (2009 a) Die Gattung Hieracium L. (Compositae) in der Region Abruzzen (Italien). Eine floristisch-taxonomische Studie. Stapfia 89: 1 - 328." type="journal article" year="2009">Gottschlich (2009a: 152)</bibRefCitation>
. The Italian endemic 
<taxonomicName authority="Belli (1897: 491)" authorityName="Belli" authorityPageNumber="491" authorityYear="1897" box="[240,627,1909,1935]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grovesianum">
<emphasis box="[240,421,1910,1935]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. grovesianum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Belli, S." box="[429,627,1909,1935]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="421 - 499" refId="ref2151" refString="Belli, S. (1897) Hieracium di Sardegna. [ser. 2] Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino 47: 421 - 499." type="journal article" year="1897">Belli (1897: 491)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the most representative taxon of that section. It is a variable species, often confused with the C European 
<taxonomicName authority="Suter (1802: 145)" authorityName="Suter" authorityPageNumber="145" authorityYear="1802" box="[556,915,1945,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lachenalii">
<emphasis box="[556,703,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. lachenalii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Suter, J. R." box="[712,915,1945,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref3247" refString="Suter, J. R. (1802) Helvetiens Flora, 2. Orell &amp; Fussli, Zurich, 504 pp." type="book" year="1802">Suter (1802: 145)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and occurs in the whole Apennine range, with its centre of diversity in the C and N Apennine (
<bibRefCitation author="Gottschlich, G. &amp; Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E." box="[681,945,1981,2007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="826 - 831" refId="ref2869" refString="Gottschlich, G., Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E. (2013) Hieracium pallidum subsp. aetnense (Asteraceae), a new subspecies from Sicily (Italy), with notes on the taxonomy of H. pallidum Biv. Plant Biosystems 147 (3): 826 - 831. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263504.2013.829882" type="journal article" year="2013">
Gottschlich 
<emphasis box="[820,877,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Hybridisation processes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belli" authorityYear="1897" box="[1273,1452,1982,2007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grovesianum">
<emphasis box="[1273,1452,1982,2007]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. grovesianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Willdenow (1803: 1588)" authorityName="Willdenow" authorityPageNumber="1588" authorityYear="1803" box="[186,640,2017,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosum">
<emphasis box="[186,351,2018,2043]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. racemosum</emphasis>
Willdenow (1803: 1588)
</taxonomicName>
with other local taxa have apparently resulted in a complex of similar morphotypes, which have recently been grouped together in 
<emphasis box="[815,843,2054,2079]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H.</emphasis>
sect G 
<emphasis box="[920,1029,2054,2079]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">rovesiana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gottschlich, G." box="[1044,1252,2053,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 328" refId="ref2675" refString="Gottschlich, G. (2009 a) Die Gattung Hieracium L. (Compositae) in der Region Abruzzen (Italien). Eine floristisch-taxonomische Studie. Stapfia 89: 1 - 328." type="journal article" year="2009">Gottschlich 2009a</bibRefCitation>
–c, 2011).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147155" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5147155" box="[136,1175,1065,1087]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" startId="4.[136,229,1065,1087]" targetBox="[227,1361,190,1041]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1175,1065,1087]" box="[136,1175,1065,1087]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,254,1065,1087]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Carbonate rocks and stony slopes of Scala di Gaudolino, the habitat of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[941,1169,1066,1087]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis box="[941,1169,1066,1087]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1133,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
Among the hitherto known taxa of 
<taxonomicName box="[609,931,1134,1160]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Grovesiana">
<emphasis box="[609,729,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[801,931,1134,1160]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Grovesiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[949,1126,1134,1159]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis box="[949,1126,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">H. terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles most closely the Sicilian endemic 
<taxonomicName authority="Caldarella, Gianguzzi &amp; Gottschlich (2014: 439)" authorityName="Caldarella, Gianguzzi &amp; Gottschlich" authorityPageNumber="439" authorityYear="2014" box="[334,1096,1169,1195]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="busambarense">
<emphasis box="[334,530,1169,1195]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">H. busambarense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Caldarella, O. &amp; Gianguzzi, L. &amp; Gottschlich, G." box="[538,1096,1169,1195]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" pagination="439 - 443" refId="ref2279" refString="Caldarella, O., Gianguzzi, L. &amp; Gottschlich, G. (2014) Hieracium busambarense, a new species of the sect. Grovesiana (Asteraceae) from Sicily (Italy). Plant Biosystems 148 (3): 439 - 443. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263504.2013.778352" type="journal article" year="2014">Caldarella, Gianguzzi &amp; Gottschlich (2014: 439)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from this species in having spotted leaves, less acute involucral bracts and by bract indumentum (more stellate hairs and less glandular hairs).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1133,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[189,455,1278,1303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis box="[189,455,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
adds to the considerable number of new endemic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1022,1142,1278,1303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1022,1142,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa recently discovered in S 
<collectingCountry box="[159,210,1313,1339]" name="Italy" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E." box="[224,570,1313,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" pagination="313 - 324" refId="ref3056" refString="Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E. (2004) Hieracium pignattianum (Asteraceae), a new species from the Madonie Mountains (N-Sicily). Bocconea 17: 313 - 324." type="journal article" year="2004">Raimondo &amp; Di Gristina 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E." box="[581,640,1313,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" pagination="86 - 92" refId="ref3095" refString="Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E. (2007) Hieracium madoniense (Asteraceae), a new species from Sicily. Plant Biosystems 141 (1): 86 - 92. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263500601153982" type="journal article" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gottschlich, G. &amp; Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E." box="[651,909,1313,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" pagination="826 - 831" refId="ref2869" refString="Gottschlich, G., Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E. (2013) Hieracium pallidum subsp. aetnense (Asteraceae), a new subspecies from Sicily (Italy), with notes on the taxonomy of H. pallidum Biv. Plant Biosystems 147 (3): 826 - 831. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263504.2013.829882" type="journal article" year="2013">
Gottschlich 
<emphasis box="[787,843,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Di Gristina, E. &amp; Gottschlich, G. &amp; Galesi, R. &amp; Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Cristaudo, A." box="[920,1174,1313,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" pagination="49 - 55" refId="ref2438" refString="Di Gristina, E., Gottschlich, G., Galesi, R., Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Cristaudo, A. (2013) Hieracium hypochoeroides subsp. montis-scuderii (Asteraceae), a new endemic subspecies from Sicily (Italy). Flora Mediterranea 23: 49 - 55." type="journal article" year="2013">
Di Gristina 
<emphasis box="[1052,1109,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Caldarella, O. &amp; Gianguzzi, L. &amp; Gottschlich, G." box="[1185,1431,1313,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" pagination="439 - 443" refId="ref2279" refString="Caldarella, O., Gianguzzi, L. &amp; Gottschlich, G. (2014) Hieracium busambarense, a new species of the sect. Grovesiana (Asteraceae) from Sicily (Italy). Plant Biosystems 148 (3): 439 - 443. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263504.2013.778352" type="journal article" year="2014">
Caldarella 
<emphasis box="[1307,1364,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
